Package: catgraph
Type: Package
Title: Weighted Association Networks for Categorical Data
Version: 0.11.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Marko", "Orosnjak", email = "marko.orosnjak@uni.lu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
  )
Description: Network-based analysis of multinomial categorical data in two
    complementary layers: a variable-level association network and a
    modality-level co-association network on factor levels. Four
    association paradigms are supported as edge weights — frequentist
    (classical and bias-corrected Cramér's V), information-theoretic
    (Normalised Mutual Information and Adjusted Mutual Information), and
    Bayesian (Dirichlet-smoothed Cramér's V) — enabling robust
    multi-paradigm comparison of categorical association structure.
    Community detection, bootstrap confidence intervals, weighted
    centrality, and permutation-based tests for cross-group structural
    differences are provided. Designed for descriptive exploration of
    joint categorical structure and for comparing categorical association
    patterns across groups, studies, or populations.
